Patch Set 3: Do not merge

@Zhi TBH, I'd prefer the sync to be a *whole* oslo-inc sync. We've discussed this a lot in the mailing list for the overall community and I'd really like to keep glance up-to-date.

The right workflow should be:

1. Patch that syncs oslo-incubator with a commit message containing the sha of the commits most relevant
2. A second patch (this one) doing whatever you need to do. 

(the -2 is because we have to wait for the oslo-patch to land, I'll remove it as soon as it does)

If we're fixing this with a migration then I don't think we should expose a new option to users, especially when the other projects don't.  We should know which migration is going to fix the utf8 encoding and force utf8 checking any time we start a migration from a db version where we expect utf8 to already be applied.
